But were not Gamalitica itself and Gaulo- nitis within Batanea? Right: but by this distinction he divides between that Batanea that was nearer Galilee, and that that was farther off. That country that lay nearest, from those noted towns of Gaulan and Gamala, he calls Gaulonitis and Gamalitica3 and that which was farther off, he calls by its own name of Batanea3 and what lies still beyond that, Tra- chonitis.

There was a time when all that whole country, which now is distinguished into these severals, had one general name of Bashan ,- which word, how it came to change into Bathan, or Batanea‚——as also, with the Targumists and Samaritam, into Bathnin and Mathnin,——any one, indifferently skilled in the Syrian tongue‚ will easily discern.
